---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Chemistry Elements — Elemental High Scorers"
  description="Chemical element words valid in Scrabble with point values. XENON 12pts, ZINC 15pts, KRYPTON 16pts, COBALT 10pts. Chemistry vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble chemistry words, xenon scrabble points, zinc scrabble word, krypton scrabble, element words scrabble, chemical names scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Chemistry Elements — Elemental High Scorers","description":"Chemical element words valid in Scrabble with point values. XENON 12pts, ZINC 15pts, KRYPTON 16pts, COBALT 10pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-chemistry-elements"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is KRYPTON a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! KRYPTON scores 16 points (K=5, R=1, Y=4, P=3, T=1, O=1, N=1). It's a noble gas element (atomic number 36). The K and Y tiles contribute 9 of the 16 points. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is ZINC worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"ZINC scores 15 points (Z=10, I=1, N=1, C=3). It's element 30 on the periodic table. At just 4 letters with the Z tile providing 10 points, ZINC is one of the most efficient Z-word plays available."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XENON valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. XENON scores 12 points (X=8, E=1, N=1, O=1, N=1) and is a noble gas (element 54). The X tile delivers 8 of the 12 points. It's a clean way to play X with common surrounding tiles."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Chemistry Elements — Elemental High Scorers</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The periodic table is hiding some serious Scrabble firepower. Element names use premium tiles naturally — ZINC drops the Z for 15 points in just 4 letters, KRYPTON uses K and Y together for 16, and XENON places the X tile cleanly among common letters. Every science student already knows these words.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KRYPTON (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZINC</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">XENON</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COBALT</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Element Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">KRYPTON — 16 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">K=5, R=1, Y=4, P=3, T=1, O=1, N=1 · 7 letters · K+Y+P triple</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Noble gas element 36, famously Superman's home planet. KRYPTON uses three mid-value tiles (K=5, Y=4, P=3) alongside four common 1-point letters. As a 7-letter word, it qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus if you use all your tiles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚗️ ZINC</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · Z=10, I=1, N=1, C=3 · Element 30</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💡 XENON</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · X=8, E=1, N=1, O=1, N=1 · Noble gas</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔵 COBALT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · C=3, O=1, B=3, A=1, L=1, T=1 · Element 27</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪙 NICKEL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · N=1, I=1, C=3, K=5, E=1, L=1 · Element 28</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Element Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ARGON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NEON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BORON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RADON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CARBON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZINC is a 4-letter Z word:</span> At 15 points from 4 tiles (3.75 per tile), ZINC has one of the best points-per-tile ratios in the game. It's short enough to fit anywhere and uses the Z tile efficiently with common I, N, C support tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KRYPTON is bingo material:</span> At exactly 7 letters, KRYPTON earns the 50-point bingo bonus if you play all tiles from your rack. That's 66 total points (16 + 50) — a game-changing play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">XENON starts with X:</span> Words beginning with X are rare and valuable. XENON places X at the start, which means you only need the right-side tiles (E, N, O, N) to connect to existing words on the board.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Element names cover <span class="text-white font-medium">all three super-premium tiles</span> — Z (ZINC), X (XENON), and K (KRYPTON, NICKEL). They also handle the awkward Y tile (KRYPTON) and B tile (COBALT). Learn these five element words and you'll have plays for every difficult tile draw.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-science/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Science</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid element word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
